			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">IMO,Beastlord is a fun class to play as an alt, quite good to solo except for a particularly weak zone between 44 and 49. Their pets only come along every 10 levels or so through the bulk of the levelling process. The procs you put on em as a buff is a really useful feature as you always have the option of putting a cold based, fire based, poison based proc on tigger depending on what you are fighting.
<br />

<br />
They also have the advantage of having a good set of shammy buffs and unlike us mages excellent pet heals. With half-way decent kit they do a fair job of Mellee as well. They're a good class, that's why you see so many of em. 
<br />

<br />
At the end of the day though playing a particular class is totally subjective. I like BL's but always come back to my mage. If you are going to play one though I'd look at Ogre's as well as the more usual Vah Shir, Ogres make pretty awesome BL's.
<br />

<br />
As for Uber. Hmmm, they have the easiest epic to get and there are a lot of good items you can solo for them. The problem in game is that everyone and his brother has a BL, I know a couple of my friends have problems getting into uber-guilds with em just because there are so many. Also while the tigger(or bear or whatever) pet DOES look nice, I duelled a friend a while back, pets only, her 62 pet against my 61 air pet, her pet with all her buffs on (plus items I'd summoned - dumb of me or what), mine with BoV,my DS, summoned items on, and my pet tore her tigger to pieces. 
<br />

<br />
That said, if there was a class that seems to have been 'blessed' by the true gods of eq (Sony) then BL is it. Now if you want to consider a BL/Mage duo pair (how I normally play these days.) THAT is uber. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
