			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've played a lot of alts, but none to really high (50+ levels) but in my opinion if you like a caster you'll generally like other casters. If you were a soloing mage you'd like the more soloable classes (necros, bsts, sks to an extent).
<br />

<br />
I personally find the melee system rather boring currently (glad to see they are changing it) and if you were a caster who did more than stand/nuke/sit you probably will too, so I'd advise against strict melee or the tanking hybrids.
<br />

<br />
Enc charming is fun, and helps train you for CotAM. Enc is my favorite alt class (especially for tradeskill reasons) and post-20 they are pretty decently fun to play.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
