			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally the fun of a mage was always the challenge. The only other character as an alt I've found with even more challenge was a bard. Constantly keeping songs up, pulling, mezzing, charming, slowing, all the time while melee'ing is great fun. 
<br />

<br />
The only bad thing about being a bard is that you can't just hit pet attack, or the "A" button and run to the bathroom while the whole group wails on a mob. (unless you don't mind coming back to "Where's the haste/slow/mana song/resists/etc" messages all over your screen). Bards are busy during combat and during downtime, no time to sit while others med, you need to be twisting those heal and mana songs, or lulling the next room full of mobs.
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
